I'm biased because my first date with my wife was at Welty's, but it's a great deli and my favorite place to go while working downtown. Huge salads, great sandwiches- the reuben is my favorite in all of New Orleans, but be careful, it is foodcoma inducing.

Welty's is a Great Deli in the CBD in the 300 Block of Camp St. Off Poydras Ave. Welty's serves a Hot Food Plate Menu daily; a variety of GOOD Salads (Chicken, Tuna & Shrimp), Soups & Sandwiches. Welty's, also do Really Good Catering for Meetings or Special Occasions.  Welty's is One of my Favorite Lunch Places in the CBD Area.😀

Favorite lunch spot downtown. Sandwiches, salads, soups and entrees to fit everyone's needs and a daily special for each too. I can't get enough of them I must say. I just need to talk my workplace into letting them cater our events.

For years I have been going to Welty's and today I found out I have been overcharged.  They charge for tap water without the customer knowing it.  They give you a receipt that is not itemized. I will never go there again and will tell all of my friends.  It is the principle of the thing, if one is on the up and up, one lets the customer know that there is a charge for water and you give an itemized receipt.

We stumbled on to welty's by accident today. It was a wonderful accident! We were greeted like family and it was all uphill from there..  I ordered the trio salad. Tuna, chicken, and curry chicken salad on a bed of romaine with eggs and tomatoes. It was a huge portion , and I didn't do it justice.. curry chicken is my new favorite! My husband got the Reuben and it looked amazing. And since there was no sandwich left I'm gonna assume that it was indeed amazing! Sometimes when you order soup and salad you leave a place hungry.. not here you don't.. the tortilla soup looks great!  All in all it was a wonderful experience and the next time I'm in the neighborhood we will certainly be back!! Thanks, from slidell.

Compliments to the Chef. Friendly staff and quality food for a reasonable price make this restaurant a must-go while in NOLA. I have to admit I find myself checking their website daily to see what surprises have been crafted in the kitchen. Their daily Specials are a great refresher to the mundane subs and salads that seem to pop up around noon at other restaurants throughout the week. I have yet to see a special repeated, even to my own dismay, so for anyone who might make Welty's a regular stop, you will never grow tired of what's on the menu.

I am a regular at this family-run establishment.  I have never had a meal there that has disappointed me! The portions are so large that a friend and I often split one entree and are very content. They have delicious, high-end daily specials and their regular daily fare is also superb! Some of my favorites lately have included the roasted pork loin with garlic mashed potatoes and the shepherd's pie, but their asian chicken salad, roasted chicken salad, gumbo and sandwiches are also wonderful. It gets a little noisy and busy during the business lunch time but it is worth the noise and the wait. If in a rush, order it over the phone and it will be ready for you when you get there. The owners are great people and the staff are very helpful. One of my all-time favorite lunch spots in NOLA!

I LOVE WELTY'S.  I was there in November and stayed right next to Welty's.  My wife and I needed a quick bite on our way out, so we decided to stop in.  Little did we know it would be one of the highlights of the trip.  Sounds crazy, maybe, but it's true.  The city of New Orleans is awesome and Welty's puts it over the top.  After the first lunch we had there, we tried to get it again on a Sunday but they are closed on weekends since it's in the business district.  So, Monday we made it a point to go get it again and it was equally delicious.  I wish I knew where they got the turkey from because it is the best turkey I have ever had.  And then combined with the melted cheese and croissant - you can't beat it.  I've now joked (or maybe it's not a joke) with people that I will find flights with a layover in N.O. so I can catch a cab and go get Welty's.  "Welty's me."
